Nimbooda is hands-down my favorite Indian Restaurant. I first discovered Nimbooda because I was on a scavenger hunt for vegan naan (it's usually made with ghee). This is one of the few places where you can get it and the garlic naan in particular is delicious.  I should also note that Nimbooda is BYOB with no corkage fee (and Prospect Heights Beer Works is literally one block away). The service is attentive and fast and they deliver.  Most importantly, the food is outstanding. There are dishes I usually don't even like that I love here (Chana Masala for example). My favorites (besides that) are: Eggplant Bhindi Bharta, Mushroom Curry, and the Saag. They are accomodating about removing dairy from vegetarian entrees that have it.  I highly recommend Nimbooda for anyone looking for Indian food in the area. As with most Indian restaurants, it's very reasonably priced as well. It's an excellent option for a large group dinner on a budget (inexpensive, delicious food and BYOB).

This is the only Indian restaurant in NYC that I've eaten at in-person more than I've gotten take-out from. It's a tiny place that's never busy inside, but then again few Indian restaurants ever are since most of the business comes from take-out/delivery.  Nimbooda's servers are incredibly hospitable and often bring out a little amuse bouche before the meal comes out (another perk to going in-person). I love the food. My favorites include the samosa chaat, chicken korma, and kandhari naan. If you have a sweet tooth and want a twist on your naan, get the kandhari naan! It's a little sweet and super buttery and SO GOOD.  BYOB. Winey Neighbor is just up the street. And if you forget to bring something beforehand, they're cool about you running out to grab a bottle.  Inside it's really cozy with an intimate vibe. I'll be back soon!
